---
title: Apricot Ancho Chicken with Roasted Potatoes and a Lemony Salad
description: Want to add tons of restaurant-level flavor to your chicken with almost no effort? Allow us to introduce you to the mighty pan sauce. Here, sweet apricot jam, savory chicken stock, and smoky ancho chili powder mingle with the fond⁠—the crispy bits and drippings left by the chicken⁠—to create a condiment that you’ll want to drizzle over everything. Speaking of, we’re serving up a side of crispy roasted potatoes that wouldn’t say no to some of this smoky sauce.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/apricot-ancho-chicken-749ca377.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/apricot-ancho-chicken-5d485c689697b1000937b7e2-b074f5f3.pdf
time required: 35 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/apricot-ancho-chicken-5d485c689697b1000937b7e2
author: Sara Heilman
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 580 kcal
  fat: 25 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 51 g
  sugar: 17 g
